Bishop Francis Wale Oke, President of the Pentecostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN) and President and Founder Sword of the Spirit Ministries Int’l, Oyo State, alongside Pastor Funso Odesola, Assistant General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) on Admin & Personnel and Continental Overseer Africa Continent 3 (South West Nigeria and Middle East) will be ministering at the annual thanksgiving service of INDEPENDENT Newspapers Limited (INL). The special event organised by INL Christian Fellowship takes place, Thursday February 10, at the company’s head office, 8 Wempco Road, off Agidingbi, opposite Agbalajobi Estate, Ogba, Ikeja, Lagos State. Mr. Yemi Adebisi, Pastor-in-charge of INL Fellowship, said the programme, tagged ‘Lift Up Your Heads O Ye Gates’, adopted from Psalms 24 verse 1, was to appreciate God for His faithfulness despite challenges. Soul Winning Is A Great Task (II) Brand Expert Tasks City Churches Against Complacency While assuring that the programme would birth a greater beginning individually and collectively, he stressed that “appreciating God for what He has done is a secret. It compels God to do the imaginable.”